=== Norm ===

# (''Slang'') [[Normal]].  The [[average]] or [[standard]].
# (''Mathematics'') A measure of length, denoted <math>|\cdot|</math> or <math>||\cdot||</math> with the following properties:
## <math>|a|>0</math> or <math>|a|=0</math> [[iff]] <math>a</math> is the [[additive identity]].
## Given a [[scalar]] <math>k</math>, <math>|ka|=|k||a|</math>, where <math>|k|</math> is the [[absolute value]] of <math>k</math>.
## Given <math>a</math> and <math>b</math>, <math>|a+b|\leq|a|+|b|</math>. (Known as the [[triangle inequality]].)
#(Australia) '''Norm''' (Usually capitalised) Male layabout, lazy inactive man. (From a character in 1980s government health promotion ads).
